2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 105
BY SENATOR JACKSON-ANDREWS
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Designates Wednesday, May 6, 2026, as Links Day at the
Louisiana State Capitol.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Wednesday, May 6, 2026, as Links Day at the Louisiana State Capitol and to
3 commend The Links, Incorporated, for their dedicated service and lasting
4 contributions to the state and its residents.
5 WHEREAS, established in 1946, The Links, Incorporated, is an international
6 not-for-profit corporation committed to enriching, sustaining, and ensuring the cultural and
7 economic survival of African Americans and persons of African ancestry; and
8 WHEREAS, the organization is one of the nation's oldest and largest volunteer
9 service organizations of women dedicated to improving the lives of others through a strong
10 focus on community service and civic engagement; and
11 WHEREAS, the mission of The Links, Incorporated, is to promote and engage in
12 educational, civic, and intercultural activities that enhance the lives of members and the
13 larger community through five program facets: Services to Youth, The Arts, National Trends
14 and Services, International Trends and Services, and Health and Human Services; and
15 WHEREAS, The Links, Incorporated, is comprised of more than seventeen thousand
16 professional women of African descent in two hundred ninety-nine chapters, located in
17 forty-one states, with seven chapters established in Louisiana, as well as the District of
18 Columbia; the Commonwealth of the Bahamas; and the United Kingdom; and
