1 WHEREAS, the Louisiana chapters of Baton Rouge, Crescent City, La Capitale,
2 Monroe-Grambling, New Orleans, Pontchartrain, and Shreveport belong to the Southern
3 Area of The Links, Incorporated, and together these chapters represent decades of leadership
4 and service throughout the state; and
5 WHEREAS, each chapter has significantly contributed to the advancement of
6 education, health equity, cultural preservation, and community development in Louisiana
7 through volunteerism and impactful programming; and
8 WHEREAS, Links Day at the Louisiana State Capitol is an advocacy project of the
9 Southern Area of The Links, Incorporated, and serves as an important opportunity for
10 members to engage with lawmakers, highlight issues affecting communities across the state,
11 and reinforce the importance of civic involvement, leadership, and public service.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
13 does hereby designate Wednesday, May 6, 2026, as Links Day at the Louisiana State Capitol
14 and does hereby commend The Links, Incorporated, for their dedicated service and lasting
15 contributions to the state of Louisiana and its residents.
